Their fourth full-length represents a summation of the different styles and directions heard on past Vetiver releases while introducing some unexpected twists. Their tunes have been described as dreamy, gentle songs that George Harrison would have written in some sunny country garden. This is a layered and rich record, with subtleties and nuances that reveal themselves with repeated listening.
